      1          /**
      2           * @file
      3           * @brief       A cross-category process for measuring time in a cycle.
      4           *
      5           * @details
      6           * The Maintain Process measures elapsed time as the number of seconds that the current step has
      7           * been running. It compares the elapsed time to the delay time specified in the parameters.
      8           *
      9           * If the process parameters include a modifier, then the delay time is the time with the modifier
     10           * applied.
     11           *
     12           * If the process parameters include a condition, then the countdown only runs while the condition
     13           * is TRUE.
     14           *
     15           * If the ADD_UNUSED_TIME option of Maintain is used, then any time that was not used up in the
     16           * previous Maintain statement is added to the time for the current Maintain statement.
     17          
     18              @startuml{Maintain_sm.jpg}
     19                  title Maintain State Machine
     20                  ' Use state = Maintain.State
     21          
     22                  [*] --> Initialize
     23          
     24                  Initialize --> Paused : evCountDownDisabled
     25                  Initialize --> CountDown : evCountDownEnabled
     26                  Initialize --> Complete : evTimeout
     27          
     28                  Paused : do / WaitForEnable()
     29                  Paused -u-> Initialize : evInitialize
     30                  Paused --> CountDown : evCountDownEnabled\n/ DecrementCounter()
     31          
     32                  CountDown : entry / CheckForTimeout()
     33                  CountDown : do / CheckIfDisabled()\n\t DecrementCounter()\n\t CheckForTimeout()
     34                  CountDown -u-> Initialize : evInitialize
     35                  CountDown -u-> Paused : evCountDownDisabled
     36                  CountDown -r-> Complete : evTimeout
     37          
     38                  Complete -u-> Initialize : evInitialize
     39              @enduml
     40          
